node.text: @manuedelamontagne And so moving how the noise seems to stop because technically we are below earth🙏🏼

Early morning run to Vietnam Veterans Memorial by land artist and architect Maya Lin.
Designed as a literal and metaphorical cut into American soil, the rising gradient of its walls progressively shelters you as you walk to its center. There, the number of names of those who lost their lives during the Vietnam War peak. There, one can reflect on this “wound that is closed and healing". There lies our collective memory.

@reinventingrid you were there in the right moment, i‘ve been there Twice but I’ve Never Seen it your way. - you are so attentive!! You run and you look 👀 and discover the same time! 🔝🔝🔝I L❤️VE your photos and your comments which reveal so such knowledge ❤️🤩
@maspor03 Thank you for saying this🙏🏼🙏🏼 I love sharing what my eyes see and hopefully encourage others to look more😘😘
@jr.artynotes Yes, very very moving. Masterpiece perfectly aligning what it needs to say, mean and look like🖤
Most impressive memorial - still on my mind
@manuedelamontagne And so moving how the noise seems to stop because technically we are below earth🙏🏼
